race.description: Ararat Rsl Sir Brudenell White Highweight Hcp
race.comment: Tough. DON STEFANO (3) has been racing at the provincials and will be better for the Mornington outing, stepping up to 3070m. Was well in the market and gets his chance over the extreme distance. Stablemate SALSITA (1) found one much too good over 2500m at Morphettville but covered the others and had good support. That sets him up for this. GUIDO GUIDO (2) was heading in the right direction in town before getting too far back as favourite at Mornington over 3050. Hard fit now and has winning claims. IN YOUR HANDS (5) placed a distant second in the same contest. Maps well and no surprise to see her in the frame.
